{
  "stem": "4361.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And this hitting and the slapping and whatnot-- came noon, and now we stand in a row, single rowed, and strangely, this time, the two barrels of what used to be just slop is the distribution of this slop into huge barrels, is being supervised by this SS.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't know how it happened, but I happen to be first in line, and I had by that time somehow organized, gotten around to have my own little tin cup.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I stand there, and he says, come-- come.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Somebody pushes me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I go.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he lifts, and as I went a couple of steps, somehow instinctively, I put both my hands behind my back, including the tin cup, at which point the SS dips the ladle into the barrel of soup, lifts it, and lets it drip back-- the soup, the liquid-- saying to me, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "This is Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I'm not thinking of Yom Kippur really in those terms.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Yes, as he did that, I was very, very hungry, but I sort of remembered the night before the chant, the And I say, nein.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He does it again, and I still keep my hands back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then he takes the ladle with the soup and splashes it in my face and calls me [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], the usual terms that the Nazis used for us-- dirty Jew, pig Jew, whatnot.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And now the soup, the liquid drips down my face, and I have this urge to at least lick it, because it's full of potatoes.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I mean he was showing it to me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "That's what he was showing to me that it wasn't a slop this time.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
